command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentTypeProperty
command.description: Updates the type and/or the value of an Equipment Type Property. This command can also be used to add Attributes to the Equipment Type Property.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentTypeProperty
command.description: Deletes an Equipment Type Property.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentConfigurationProperty
command.description: Updates the value of an Equipment Configuration Property. This command can also be used to add Attributes to the Equipment Configuration Property.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateEquipmentType
command.description: Creates an Equipment Type.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentType
command.description: Deletes an Equipment Type. It is not possible to delete the Equipment Type if it has been used to create an Equipment Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.FreezeEquipmentType
command.description: Configures the Equipment Type to be read-only by setting the *IsFrozen* attribute to True. This means that the Equipment Type cannot be edited and modified.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UnfreezeEquipmentType
command.description: c

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentType
command.description: Updates one or more properties of an Equipment Type.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateEquipmentConfiguration
command.description: Creates an Equipment Configuration using an Equipment Type as template.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentConfiguration
command.description: Deletes an Equipment Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.SetEquipmentConfigurationLocation
command.description: Sets the Location of an Equipment Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentConfiguration
command.description: Updates one or more properties of an Equipment Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.FreezeEquipmentConfiguration
command.description: Configures the Equipment Configuration to be read-only by setting the *IsFrozen* attribute to True. This means that the Equipment Configuration cannot be edited and modified.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UnfreezeEquipmentConfiguration
command.description: Removes the read-only setting from the Equipment Configuration by setting the *IsFrozen* attribute to False. This means that the Equipment Configuration can be edited and modified.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateEquipmentGroupConfiguration
command.description: Creates an Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentGroupConfiguration
command.description: Deletes the specified Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.AssociateEquipmentConfigurationsWithEquipmentGroupConfiguration
command.description: Adds a list of Equipment Configurations to a specified Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.AssociateEquipmentGroupConfigurationsWithEquipmentConfiguration
command.description: Adds the specified Equipment Configuration to different Equipment Group Configurations.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.SetEquipmentTypeAsDefault
command.description: Sets the specified Equipment Type as default template for the creation of the Equipment Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DisassociateEquipmentConfigurationsFromEquipmentGroupConfiguration
command.description: Removes a list of Equipment Configuration from a specified Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DisassociateEquipmentGroupConfigurationsFromEquipmentConfiguration
command.description: Removes the specified Equipment Configuration from the specified list of Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateEquipmentConfigurationByDefaultEquipmentType
command.description: Creates an Equipment Configuration using the default Equipment Type, if the EquipmentTypeNId is not specified.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateEquipmentGraphType
command.description: Creates a new Equipment Graph Type.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentGraphType
command.description: Updates one or more properties of an Equipment Graph Type.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentGraphType
command.description: Deletes an Equipment Graph Type.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateEquipmentGraphConfiguration
command.description: Creates a new Equipment Graph Configuration. The type of Equipment Graph Configuration is specified by the **type** parameter, whose possible values are **Hierarchy** and **Flow**.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentGraphConfiguration
command.description: Updates one or more properties of an Equipment Graph Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentGraphConfiguration
command.description: Deletes an Equipment Graph Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateEquipmentGraphNodeConfiguration
command.description: Creates the Configuration of an Equipment Graph Node. If you specify both the parameters **EquipmentConfigurationNId** and **EquipmentGroupConfigurationNId**, the specified Equipment Configuration must belong to the specified Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentGraphNodeConfiguration
command.description: Deletes the Equipment Graph Node Configuration. The command execution succeeds only if the Equipment Graph Node Configuration you are deleting is not linked to other Equipment Graph Node Configurations.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateEquipmentGraphLinkConfiguration
command.description: Creates the Configuration of a Link, which is the connection between two Equipment Graph Nodes, in an Equipment Graph. The Equipment Graph Nodes may represent either an Equipment or an Equipment Group.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentGraphLinkConfiguration
command.description: Updates one or more properties of an Equipment Graph Link Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentGraphLinkConfiguration
command.description: Deletes an Equipment Graph Link Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateHierarchyEquipmentNodeConfigurations
command.description: Creates one or more Node Configurations of an Equipment Hierarchy.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateHierarchyEquipmentNodeConfiguration
command.description: Updates the link of a Hierarchy Equipment Node Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteHierarchyEquipmentNodeConfiguration
command.description: Deletes a Hierarchy Equipment Node Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentTypePropertyAttribute
command.description: Updates the type and/or the value of an Equipment Type Property Attribute.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentConfigurationPropertyAttribute
command.description: Updates the Attribute Value of an Equipment Configuration Property Attribute.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.BulkImportEquipmentGraphConfiguration
command.description: Manages an Equipment Graph Configuration. If the Equipment Graph Configuration, specified by NId, exists, the command updates its name and/or description, the lists of its node and its links; otherwise, it creates a new Equipment Graph Configuration. In this latter case, if the *EquipmentGraphLinkConfigurations* list contains links, the *EquipmentGraphNodeConfigurations* list must not be empty.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateEquipmentGroupConfiguration
command.description: Updates one or more properties of an Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.BulkImportEquipmentHierarchy
command.description: Imports a json file containing the structure of the Hierarchy to be associated to the Equipment Graph Configuration identified by *EquipmentGraphConfigurationId*. If the structure is empty, the data contained in the json file will be used to build the Hierarchy; otherwise the data will be used to modify the existing structure.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentConfigurationProperty
command.description: Deletes an Equipment Configuration Property.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentTypeStateMachine
command.description: Delete a State Machine From Equipment Type

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.AddEquipmentTypeStateMachines
command.description: Add a list of StateMachine to an EquipmentType

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.AddEquipmentConfigurationStateMachines
command.description: Add a list of StateMachine to an EquipmentConfiguration

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentConfigurationStateMachine
command.description: Delete a State Machine From Equipment Configuration

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.MigrateEquipmentConfigurationStateMachine
command.description: It permits to create EquipmentConfigurationStateMachines coming from the Runtime Equipment, in order to manage the new multi status behaviour.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.MigrateEquipmentTypeStateMachine
command.description: It permits to create EquipmentTypeStateMachines, in order to manage the new multi status behaviour.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.FreezeEquipmentGroupConfiguration
command.description: The primary key identifier of the Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.UnfreezeEquipmentGroupConfiguration
command.description: Removes the read-only setting from the Equipment Group Configuration by setting the attribute IsFrozen to False.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.AssociateChildrenEquipmentGroupConfWithEquipmentGroupConf
command.description: Associates a Equipment Group Configuration to a list of children Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.AssociateParentsEquipmentGroupConfWithEquipmentGroupConf
command.description: Associates an Equipment Group Configuration to a list of parents Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DisassociateChildrenEquipmentGroupConfFromEquipmentGroupConf
command.description: Removes the association between one or more children Equipment Group Configuration and an Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DisassociateParentsEquipmentGroupConfFromEquipmentGroupConf
command.description: Removes the association between one or more Parents Equipment Group Configuration and an Equipment Group Configuration.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateEquipmentLevel
command.description: Creates an Equipment Configuration Level.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.FreezeEquipmentLevel
command.description: Configures the Equipment Configuration Level to be read-only by setting the *IsFrozen* attribute to True. This means that the Equipment Configuration Level cannot be edited and modified.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.MigrateEquipmentConfigurationLocation
command.description: It permits to create an Equipment Configuration Hierarchy when a Location is defined

command.description: Deletes an Equipment Type Property Attribute.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteEquipmentConfigurationPropertyAttribute
command.description: Deletes an Equipment Configuration Property Attribute.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Events.EquipmentGraphNodeConfigurationUpdated
event.description: This event is fired when an Equipment Graph Node Configuration is changed, for example on creation, update and deletion.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Events.EquipmentGraphLinkConfigurationUpdated
event.description: This event is fired when an Equipment Graph Link Configuration is updated.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Events.EquipmentConfigurationUpdated
event.description: This event is fired when an Equipment Configuration is changed, for example on creation, and deletion.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Events.EquipmentConfigurationGroupUpdated
event.description: This event is fired when an Equipment Configuration Group is changed, for example on creation, deletion, association and disassociation.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Events.EquipmentConfigurationPropertyUpdated
event.description: This event is fired when the value of an Equipment Configuration Property is changed.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Events.EquipmentConfigurationPropertyAttributeUpdated
event.description: This event is fired when the value of an Equipment Configuration Property Attribute is changed.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Events.EquipmentGraphConfigurationUpdated
event.description: This event is fired when an Equipment Graph Configuration is updated.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.EQU_MS.MSModel.Events.EquipmentConfigurationStateMachineUpdated
event.description: This event is fired when an Equipment Configuration State Machine is changed, for example on creation, deletion.
